events.name: Golden State Warriors at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 21 points and 10 assists in his annual homecoming game, and the Golden State Warriors pulled away in the second half to defeat the Charlotte Hornets 119-101 on Monday night for their sixth win in seven games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 21 in homecoming game to lift Warriors past Hornets 119-101

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 21 of his 34 points in the second half, and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Philadelphia 76ers 119-102 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trail Blazers pull away in the second half to beat the 76ers 119-102

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo had 19 points and 15 rebounds to break Miami's franchise record for double-doubles, and the Heat cruised to a 106-90 victory over the NBA-worst Washington Wizards on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo becomes Heat franchise double-double leader in 106-90 win over Wizards

headlines.description: — Caris LeVert made a layup as time expired, finishing with 25 points as the Atlanta Hawks rallied to beat the Memphis Grizzlies 132-130 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeVert's last-second bucket gives Hawks a 132-130 win over the Grizzlies

events.name: Houston Rockets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 51 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Houston Rockets 137-128 on Monday night for their 50th win of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 51 as Thunder top Rockets 137-128 for 50th win

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 22 points and DeMar DeRozan added 20, each sitting out the fourth quarter, as the Sacramento Kings beat Dallas 122-98 Monday night with the Mavericks <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings dominant in 122-98 win over Mavericks, who lose Irving to left knee sprain

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 29 points, nine assists and four steals, and the Detroit Pistons beat the Utah Jazz 134-106 on Monday night for their 10th win in 11 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons rout Jazz 134-106 and have 10 wins in 11 games for first time since 2007-08
